Package: bleval
Title: Bayesian Evaluation for Latent Variable Models
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person(given="Xiaohui", family="Luo", role=c("aut", "cre"),
                    email="xiaohui_luo@mail.bnu.edu.cn",
                    comment=c(ORCID="0000-0002-6462-0220")),
             person(given="Jieyuan", family="Dong", role="aut")
             )
Description: The bleval package provides tools for evaluating Bayesian latent 
    variable models, such as SEMs, IRT models, and MLMs. It uses adaptive 
    Gauss-Hermite quadrature to approximate marginal likelihoods by integrating out 
    latent variables, supporting the computation of DIC, WAIC, LOOIC, and 
    fully marginal likelihoods for Bayes factors. With user-friendly functions 
    and step-by-step guidance, bleval facilitates the practical implementation 
    of Bayesian model evaluation, making it accessible for applied researchers 
    in psychology and related fields.
